@Chapter Linear closures of path categories and their quotients

This chapter describes the construction of linear closures of path categories and their quotients.
A linear closure of a category $C$ over a ring $k$ is a category whose objects are the same as $C$
but whose morphisms are formal $k$-linear combinations of morphisms in $C$.

